"""
# Browser Script Module

Integrates script execution (JavaScript and Simple) with the browser engine.
Provides ScriptHost for managing JS/Simple code execution, event loops, and console output.

## Components
- ScriptHost: Top-level execution host managing code execution, event loop, and console buffer
- EventLoop: Macrotask queue and rAF scheduling for async operations
- ConsoleBuffer: Ring buffer for console.log output (512 entries)
- SimpleScript: Executor for Simple language code in the browser

References:
- M15: Browser engine integration milestone
- REQ-1, REQ-4, REQ-5, REQ-6: Script execution requirements
- AC-1, AC-3, AC-4, AC-5: Acceptance criteria for script subsystem
"""

#![allow(REQC001)]

pub use std.gc_async_mut.gpu.browser_engine.script.script_host.{ScriptHost}
pub use std.gc_async_mut.gpu.browser_engine.script.event_loop.{EventLoop}
pub use std.gc_async_mut.gpu.browser_engine.script.console_buffer.{ConsoleBuffer, ConsoleEntry}
pub use std.gc_async_mut.gpu.browser_engine.script.simple_script.{SimpleScriptExecutor}
